President Biden has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key roles in the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Access Board and the Board of Visitors to the U.S. Naval Academy.

The Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Access Board is an independent federal agency that promotes equality for people with disabilities through accessible design and the development of guidelines and standards. The appointees to this board include Elver Ariza-Silva, an advocate for people with disabilities; Heather Dowdy, an expert in accessible technology; Gregory S. Fehribach, a leader in accessibility and inclusion; Mozhdeh Amelia Hamraie, a disabled designer and scholar; Hannah Raissa Iba√±ez, a senior staff attorney focusing on tenant defense; Alexis Ander Kashar, a civil rights attorney and business leader; KR Liu, an advocate for disability inclusion; Benjamin William Julian Nadolsky, a consultant specializing in education and disability rights; and Madeline Rose Ruvolo, a transportation planner.

The Board of Visitors to the U.S. Naval Academy is responsible for evaluating various aspects of the academy. The appointees to this board include General John R. Allen, the 8th President of the Brookings Institution; Dr. Paul J. Angelo, a fellow for Latin America Studies at the Council on Foreign Relations; President Emeritus Robert E. Clark II, the former President of Wesley College; Admiral Michelle J. Howard, a retired Navy admiral; Lieutenant Commander John S. McCain IV, a reserve Naval Aviator; and Lieutenant Colonel Amy McGrath, a former Marine Corps pilot.

These appointments reflect President Biden's commitment to promoting accessibility and inclusion for people with disabilities and ensuring the success of the U.S. Naval Academy.